[
    {
        "content": "<p>At the moment <code>pin-init</code> provides the following trait:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">trait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">InPlaceInit</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>: <span class=\"nb\">Sized</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// Use the given initializer to in-place initialize a `T`.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// If `T: !Unpin` it will not be able to move afterwards.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">pin_init</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">init</span>: <span class=\"nc\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PinInit</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nc\">error</span>::<span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">Error</span>: <span class=\"nb\">From</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// Use the given initializer to in-place initialize a `T`.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">init</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">init</span>: <span class=\"nc\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Init</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nc\">error</span>::<span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">Error</span>: <span class=\"nb\">From</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>it is implemented by <code>Box</code> and <code>UniqueArc</code>.</p>\n<p>My current problem is that this references the <code>error::Result</code>, i.e. the kernel <code>Error</code> type.<br>\nAs I also want to publish this as a standalone crate - and the more rusty pattern is to allow arbitrary error types, I have to find a different error type. However, that is not as easy as using <code>Result&lt;_, E&gt;</code>, since inside of <code>pin_init</code> and <code>init</code>, I want to e.g. allocate a <code>Box</code>, so I first tried to do this (only showing <code>init</code> for simplicity):</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">trait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">InPlaceInit</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>: <span class=\"nb\">Sized</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">init</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">init</span>: <span class=\"nc\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Init</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">E</span>: <span class=\"nb\">From</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">AllocError</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This works, but places a type requirement on the initializer. Now one cannot do</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nb\">Box</span>::<span class=\"n\">init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">init</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}));</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>since <code>init!</code> returns <code>impl Init&lt;Foo, Infallible&gt;</code>.</p>\n<p>My next try was this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">trait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">InPlaceInit</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>: <span class=\"nb\">Sized</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">init</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Ei</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">init</span>: <span class=\"nc\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Init</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Ei</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">E</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">E</span>: <span class=\"nb\">From</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">AllocError</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">E</span>: <span class=\"nb\">From</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Ei</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This is better, since now one could theoretically do the above example with <code>Foo</code>, but <code>AllocError: From&lt;Infallible&gt;</code> is not satisfied (I think this could be added easily, I asked a question about this on the rust-zulip, but have not gotten an answer).</p>\n<p>Does anyone have any other ideas?</p>",
        "id": 340404702,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1678291883
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also, should I change the implementation in the kernel to use this one as well? It will still allow using <code>Error</code>, but might result in worse type inference (sigh), since it permits more freely choosing the error type.</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"413824\">@Gary Guo</span> <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"412316\">@bjorn3</span> could you guys have a look at this?</p>",
        "id": 340404797,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1678291910
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"546447\">y86</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/pin-init.20.60InPlaceInit.60/near/340404797\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Also, should I change the implementation in the kernel to use this one as well? It will still allow using <code>Error</code>, but might result in worse type inference (sigh), since it permits more freely choosing the error type.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>You can also introduce the current version, and improve it in the future.</p>",
